The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Port staff held for forgery 

 A STAFF REPORTER

 The CID on Thursday arrested a Calcutta Port Trust employee, Tapan Chakraborty, for his alleged involvement in the fake marksheet racket.

 ?Chakraborty, a clerk, was arrested at his Dunlop home, which was used for printing fake marksheets and other documents,? said Soumen Mitra, deputy inspector-general, CID. The number of people behind bars in the case goes up to 15.

 Investigating officers said more arrests are likely in the next week. ?We are in touch with police in neighbouring states like Bihar and Jharkhand,? said an officer.

 Meanwhile, a police team from Siwan, in Bihar, arrived in the city on Thursday and interrogated Mohammad Aslam Rustam Khan, the alleged kingpin of the racket. Khan, an aide of Md Shahabuddin, the controversial MP from Siwan district, was arrested in Kamarhati on Saturday.




